included.description:
Completionmatters.org is a site for educators and administrators who are working to improve graduation rates. Though new video content is regularly added, the site was not creating an active community or displaying content effectively. It needed a redesign.

Role:

I first redesigned an isolated video playback interface, but the need to have video content better integrated into the site itself quickly became obvious.

I then worked with ISKME content experts to redesign the interaction of the whole site. An outside graphic design agency had created the basic site styling that I applied to main pages.
included.title: CompletionMatters.org Redesign

included.description:
Created in partnership with Achieve.org, this tool allows trained educators to evaluate Open Educational Resources on OERCommons.org. 

The task requires evaluators to synthesize complex information: descriptions of each area for evaluation, definitions of each rating, related common core standards and then the resource itself.

Role: 

I was the interaction and graphic designer for this project, working with OERCommons' remotely located developer. Though I did not work directly with Achieve, I integrated feedback and advocated for good usability principles.
included.title: Achieve Open Educational Resource Evaluator

included.description: With a team of two other students, I planned and conducted six evaluations of Domino's Pizza intranet, Domino's Live. The intranet site contained a wiki with training materials, a blog and forums. The site serves Domino's Pizza employees from many levels of the company, though our primary focus was on general managers, store managers and franchisees in the United States. Our evaluations helped prepare the site for additional content being merged from another system.
included.title: Usability Research: Domino's Pizza Live
